{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ee0e9199-1fc8-4eff-b582-53e67d84aa44","content":"No workflow files found in the current directory. Since I can't see your specific workflow, here's what you need to change to switch to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### 1. Add `id-token: write` permission to your publish job\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # Required for OIDC\n      contents: read\n```\n\n### 2. Replace `dotnet nuget push` with the trusted publishing step\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg \\\n    --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} \\\n    --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg \\\n    --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nNo `--api-key` needed — the OIDC token is used automatically once configured on nuget.org.\n\n### 3. Configure nuget.org (one-time setup)\n\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**\n2. Add a new trusted publisher:\n   - **Repository owner**: your GitHub org/user\n   - **Repository name**: your repo name\n   - **Workflow filename**: e.g. `publish.yml`\n   - **(Optional)** lock to a specific branch or environment\n\n### 4. Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret\n\nOnce trusted publishing works, delete the secret from your repo settings.\n\nWould you like me to make these changes to a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"188643c8-f79d-4a5c-8786-b9ea33eb1f1e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no workflow files in the current directory. Let me check what's in the directory at all.","outputTokens":436,"requestId":"1FCE:834FC:BBF885:DCAB80:69FE861D"},"id":"2adcffd8-d5bc-4713-82a9-ca590225649d","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:56:07.774Z","parentId":"b35e4853-f4e3-45d6-a126-7d9c73ba1c39"}
